(38, 'How to Choose The Perfect Locksmith to Work on your Security', 'how-to-choose-the-perfect-locksmith-to-work-on-your-security', '<p>It&rsquo;s easy to get scammed nowadays especially when you&rsquo;re not aware. Many people have been victims of fake locksmith scams like mainly, getting overcharged when the job is simple enough. Or paying a locksmith that couldn&rsquo;t even get the job done. There are a lot of ways to get scammed, and you shouldn&rsquo;t be one of the many to get scammed.</p>\r\n<p>It&rsquo;s difficult to tell the difference between a fake and a legitimate locksmith since anyone can pick locks. But you can able to tell the difference between the two when a professional locksmith can do all types of locks without doing any damages. The key to choosing the best locksmith is doing your research beforehand. This is an advantage when having an emergency because you would be ready with the number of a locksmith. While looking for a locksmith during an emergency will not help you get the perfect one because of the rush.</p>\r\n<p>When doing research, make sure that all the locksmiths you&rsquo;re going to choose are certified. Being certified means having high-level skills and the knowledge because it is a highly specialized career. Your security and protection all depend on how they can properly install or repair locks, and they&rsquo;re the one who will keep your home and business secure. They should have the training and expertise when it comes to security. Ask about their credentials like their experiences, years in the business, their reputation, and services.</p>\r\n<p>Always choose the company that has 24 hours emergency services because you&rsquo;ll never know when you&rsquo;re going to need them. Make sure also that they have a wide range of services for all types of locks whether for residential, commercial, and automotive because it&rsquo;s not only your home will have problems about locks.</p>\r\n<p>Ask upfront for a quote or estimates. If they have given you estimates but has increased before the service, it&rsquo;s clear that they&rsquo;re not the one to choose. Pricing depends upon the services and the types of locks you have. Thus, it&rsquo;s best to ask for a quote before availing their services.</p>\r\n<p>When in doubt, don&rsquo;t think twice about calling the company. It&rsquo;s them who you will entrust the protection of your home or business. If you have any questions, don&rsquo;t hesitate to ask. You have to feel comfortable when you trust a locksmith. Otherwise, don&rsquo;t choose until you are fully satisfied with what you choose.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>', 'It’s easy to get scammed nowadays especially when you’re not aware. Many people have been victims of fake locksmith scams like mainly, getting overcharged when the job is simple enough.', 'post', 'locksmith expert, the best locksmith, choosing the best locksmith', 'It’s easy to get scammed nowadays especially when you’re not aware. Many people have been victims of fake locksmith scams like mainly, getting overcharged when the job is simple enough.', 'a:1:{i:0;s:13:"Uncategorized";}', 'locksmith expert, the best locksmith, choosing the best locksmith', NULL, 'admin', 0, 1, '2017-10-12 04:21:03', NULL),
(39, 'Is your home at risk of a break-in?', 'is-your-home-at-risk-of-a-break-in', '<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">Worried that your home might get robbed anytime soon? Is your home says open invitation for burglars and robbers to break in? If your gut tells you that your home is a beacon that sends signals to burglars, then you might be right. Here are known common facts on why your home can be a potential break-in.</span></p>\r\n<ol>\r\n<li><span style="font-weight: 400;">Depending on the landscape of your house, it can attract burglars if you have trees, hedges, or bushes that provide hiding spots. They may make your home look beautiful but can attract burglars.</span></li>\r\n<li><span style="font-weight: 400;">Newspapers and mails are piling up. When they are starting to pile up on your mailbox or front porch, it tells that there are no occupants to take them in. </span></li>\r\n<li><span style="font-weight: 400;">Tall grass and trash bins. Unmowed lawn and trash bins that are full is a sign of occupants in vacation. </span></li>\r\n<li><span style="font-weight: 400;">Sure, curb appeal is attractive but showing off that you&rsquo;re wealthy can invite unwanted guests inside. Fancy exteriors with a colorful paint job of your house or appealing ornaments only increase the risk of having a break-in.</span></li>\r\n<li><span style="font-weight: 400;">Security measures are hidden. If you own an advanced security system, it&rsquo;s better to let them know that you have one than hiding it. It&rsquo;s much safer than letting them try to enter even if you have security measures.</span></li>\r\n<li><span style="font-weight: 400;">A home that has no light turned on in the middle of the night is a magnet for burglars. It shows that there is no activity going on making it look like there&rsquo;s no one home. Even a home that is dark even outside is the perfect place for a burglary to happen.</span></li>\r\n<li><span style="font-weight: 400;">Spare keys are hidden in spots you think that are not obvious. You may think no one else will find your spare key under that rock or above the gutter but experienced burglars can find these keys whenever you hide them.</span></li>\r\n</ol>', 'Worried that your home might get robbed anytime soon? Is your home says open invitation for burglars and robbers to break in?', 'post', 'residential locksmith, home safety', 'Worried that your home might get robbed anytime soon? Is your home says open invitation for burglars and robbers to break in?', 'a:1:{i:0;s:21:"Residential Locksmith";}', 'residential locksmith, home safety', NULL, 'admin', 0, 1, '2017-10-13 04:57:56', NULL),
(40, 'Lock Change Service', 'lock-change-service', '<h3>Changing The Locks On A Rental Property</h3>\r\n<p>Many people don&rsquo;t realize the danger of moving into a new rental property. Sure, it would feel great because of a new beginning, but because a rental property has been with many previous tenants, you never know how many copies of the key of your lock were distributed to their friends, family, and whatnot. These distributed keys will provide access for unwanted guests to your place, compromising your safety and security.</p>\r\n<p>As of now, there is no exact law about landlords replacing locks when a new tenant moves in. But it is required for every tenant moving out of the property; the key must be surrendered to the landlord or property management. But even though the previous tenant returned the key, copies of this key are floating around waiting for your property to be opened by someone you don&rsquo;t know.</p>\r\n<p>So when you move into a new property, make sure to change your locks. But before doing so, you have to discuss this matter with your landlord or property management. You&rsquo;ll have a good chance to allow you to change your locks because they want to assure you that their building is safe and want to make you feel comfortable. You just have to make sure that your newly replaced lock&rsquo;s key has a copy for your landlord.</p>', 'When you move into a new property, make sure to change your locks. But before doing so, you have to discuss this matter with your landlord or property management. ', 'page', 'Lock Change Service, Changing The Locks On A Rental Property', 'When you move into a new property, make sure to change your locks. But before doing so, you have to discuss this matter with your landlord or property management. ', NULL, NULL, NULL, 'admin', 1, 1, '2017-10-16 03:45:26', '2017-10-17 04:49:17'),
(41, 'Car Key Replacement', 'car-key-replacement', '<h3>Electronic Keys For Cars Replacement</h3>\r\n<p>It&rsquo;s frustrating when a car lockout occurs especially when it is at the most inconvenient time. Like for example, you&rsquo;re late for a meeting, and suddenly, your electronic keys don&rsquo;t work anymore with your car.</p>\r\n<p>Electronic keys have become high-tech to improve the security of a car. Newer models of vehicles today features keys that have their transponder to communicate their matching cars. A car won&rsquo;t be able to start if the key used doesn''t match.</p>\r\n<p>This can be very bothersome in case your key got lost. You can solve this issue by going to a dealer to have your key replaced and programmed that could cost up to $200-$500 depending on the brand and model.</p>\r\n<p>If you want the less-expensive approach, you can find a replacement online that could cost only up to less than $200 including the cutting and programming process by a locksmith if necessary.</p>\r\n<p>One better way to replace your key immediately and can be cheaper than going to the dealer, you can call for a reputable and a trusted locksmith. Some locksmiths offer services that replace electronic keys on-site, fast. They will provide everything you need and get the job done efficiently. This way, it is much faster and affordable than a dealer.</p>', 'Electronic keys have become high-tech to improve the security of a car. Newer models of vehicles today features keys that have their transponder to communicate their matching cars. A car won’t be able to start if the key used doesn''t match.', 'page', 'Car Key Replacement, Electronic Keys For Cars Replacement', 'Electronic keys have become high-tech to improve the security of a car. Newer models of vehicles today features keys that have their transponder to communicate their matching cars. A car won’t be able to start if the key used doesn''t match.', NULL, NULL, NULL, 'admin', 1, 1, '2017-10-16 03:45:51', '2017-10-17 04:26:02'),
(42, '24 Hour Locksmith', '24-hour-locksmith', '<h3><strong>24 Hour Emergency Locksmith Service</strong></h3>\r\n<p>You never know when a mishap or the inevitable might happen. You might be arriving your home from a party at 3 in the morning and all of a sudden your keys are not there. You&rsquo;re hopeless and began to panic until you did something foolish like breaking your window just to get in.</p>\r\n<p>We don&rsquo;t usually call for a locksmith on a daily basis or not very often, but at times like this is the most reasonable reason to call for a locksmith. Not many people require having their locks replace or install, lose and damage keys their keys every day. But they are our heroes when we need their service.</p>\r\n<p>24-hour emergency locksmiths are available anytime so that when you need them, they will be there to help you. Emergency or not, an emergency locksmith will get to your location as soon as possible so the customer won&rsquo;t wait too long or call for another service. They will arrive with their complete tools and equipment so any problems they encounter will be handled professionally and with expertise giving relief to the customer.</p>\r\n<p>So when there is a lock issue that needs to be resolved quickly, call for a reputable locksmith. 24-hour emergency locksmiths will always be at your disposal anywhere you are even at the oddest places and time.</p>', '24-hour emergency locksmiths are available anytime so that when you need them, they will be there to help you. Emergency or not, an emergency locksmith will get to your location as soon as possible so the customer won’t wait too long or call for another service. ', 'page', '24 Hour Locksmith, 24 Hour Emergency Locksmith Service', '24-hour emergency locksmiths are available anytime so that when you need them, they will be there to help you. Emergency or not, an emergency locksmith will get to your location as soon as possible so the customer won’t wait too long or call for another service. ', NULL, NULL, NULL, 'admin', 1, 1, '2017-10-16 03:46:32', '2017-10-17 04:22:20'),
(43, 'Replacement Keys For Cars', 'replacement-keys-for-cars', '<h3>Replacement Keys For Cars With Chip</h3>\r\n<p>Over the years, there have been so many improvements with cars especially when it comes to security. An old vehicle may rely on its key for locking and the opening of doors and the ignition. While newer car models don&rsquo;t need to insert the key to unlock the door or start the car, but rather through the use of a remote. It improves the convenience and security of the car.</p>\r\n<p>Car keys today are not the same as the keys before. They are called transponder keys which contain chips to communicate with their matching cars. A transponder key has its own chip that has a unique code and will transmit this to the car&rsquo;s computer. When the code matches with the car, the car will start. Otherwise, if the code is wrong, then the car will not start.</p>\r\n<p>So what if you lose your transponder key? Surely, you will have a frustrating experience when this happens. You won&rsquo;t be able to access your car especially when it is the worst time like you&rsquo;re late for a job interview. But it&rsquo;s not just you who would lose the keys because it&rsquo;s more common than you think.</p>\r\n<p>You can quickly solve this solution by calling a professional locksmith. Locksmiths are not only for homes or building, but they also specialize in car locks. A locksmith has all the complete equipment and tools to provide you a replacement key and have the key program so that it could match your car. So don&rsquo;t let panic take over you completely, there&rsquo;s always a problem with every solution. Call your local locksmith to get your keys replaced.</p>', 'Car keys today are not the same as the keys before. They are called transponder keys which contain chips to communicate with their matching cars. A transponder key has its own chip that has a unique code and will transmit this to the car’s computer. ', 'page', 'Replacement Keys For Cars, Replacement Keys For Cars With Chip', 'Car keys today are not the same as the keys before. They are called transponder keys which contain chips to communicate with their matching cars. A transponder key has its own chip that has a unique code and will transmit this to the car’s computer. When the code matches with the car, the car will start. ', NULL, NULL, NULL, 'admin', 1, 1, '2017-10-16 03:47:10', '2017-10-17 04:29:46'),
(44, 'Ignition Key Replacement', 'ignition-key-replacement', '<h3>Ignition Key Replacement Locksmith</h3>\r\n<p>The ignition key is used to start the car by inserting the key into the ignition switch. It is obviously needed to move the car. But sometimes, mishaps can happen like damaging your key or the switch, lost the key, stolen key, or problems with the lock cylinder such as getting your key stuck.</p>\r\n<p>This could be a huge problem especially when the key is a transponder that has a chip inside. You can&rsquo;t simply replace a transponder key because it the chip inside has a unique code that matches the car&rsquo;s computer. Using a key with the wrong chip won&rsquo;t start the car.</p>\r\n<p>For you to able to fix this problem, you can contact your trusted locksmith. A professional locksmith has all the equipment and tools he needs to make a replacement for your ignition key, transponder or not. This is more convenient than going to the dealership because it costs more and can take weeks to replace your key. A locksmith can get to your location wherever you are, and if they offer 24-hour emergency service, then you don&rsquo;t have to worry getting stranded in the late hours of an evening.</p>\r\n<p>So if you there&rsquo;s an issue with your ignition key, call for your local and reputable locksmith. They will get to your location as fast as they can and will provide you a working ignition key.</p>', 'The ignition key is used to start the car by inserting the key into the ignition switch. It is obviously needed to move the car. But sometimes, mishaps can happen like damaging your key or the switch, lost the key, stolen key, or problems with the lock cylinder such as getting your key stuck.', 'page', 'Ignition Key Replacement, Ignition Key Replacement Locksmith', 'The ignition key is used to start the car by inserting the key into the ignition switch. It is obviously needed to move the car. But sometimes, mishaps can happen like damaging your key or the switch, lost the key, stolen key, or problems with the lock cylinder such as getting your key stuck.', NULL, NULL, NULL, 'admin', 1, 1, '2017-10-16 03:48:13', '2017-10-17 04:34:47'),
(45, 'Remote Car Keys Replacement', 'remote-car-keys-replacement', '<h3>Cheap Replacement Remote Car Keys</h3>\r\n<p>As a car owner, it is always vital to remember that your car keys are important. Without your keys, the car will not obviously start. But in case your keys got stolen, damaged, or lost, there are some options to consider in replacing your car keys. But for the majority of us, we will always go for the cheap option rather than spend a huge amount of cash just to replace a key.</p>\r\n<p>One option you can consider is going to the dealership depending on the brand of your car. There is no problem with dealerships replacing your keys, but the main concern is that it is expensive and time-consuming. Depending on the brand and model, it can take more than $200.</p>\r\n<p>The cheaper option is hiring a professional locksmith. No matter what type of key you have whether it is a regular key, key fob, or a transponder key, a professional locksmith can provide you a replacement on the same day you hire him. A locksmith won&rsquo;t need the original key if you can&rsquo;t provide one because it&rsquo;s part of their service for people who are getting a car lockout. They can even program your new key fob and transponder key to ensure it is compatible with the car.</p>\r\n<p>Rather than going to the dealership, call for your local locksmith. Not only it is affordable and cheaper, but you will also receive your newly replaced key quickly. Your locksmith will assure you that your key is fully compatible with your car.</p>', 'Remote Car Keys Replacement', 'page', 'Remote Car Keys Replacement, Cheap Replacement Remote Car Keys', 'Remote Car Keys Replacement', NULL, NULL, NULL, 'admin', 1, 1, '2017-10-16 03:48:28', '2017-10-17 04:36:46'),
(46, 'Programmable Car Keys Replacement', 'programmable-car-keys-replacement', '<h3>Programmable Car Keys Replacement</h3>\r\n<p>It&rsquo;s vital for any car owner to secure their cars and be protected at all times. In the past, keys were simply keys that are used to open the locks and start the cars. Today, keys have chips inside them such as key fobs and transponder keys.</p>\r\n<p>The chip inside of a key emits a signal that matches the car&rsquo;s computer for it to start. If the wrong chip is used, then the car won&rsquo;t start. This has present many advantages that have been preventing any car from being stolen. But what if you lost your car keys?</p>\r\n<p>There is nothing to be worried about because you can call a professional locksmith to replace your car keys. Even if you don&rsquo;t have the original key, a locksmith can provide you a key and will program it to match your car. A locksmith has all the specialized tools and equipment ready for cutting and programming a car key.</p>\r\n<p>This is better than going to a dealership because it can get quite expensive and will take weeks before obtaining your key while a locksmith can work on your key on the same day. So if you need any key to be programmed, call your local locksmith and he will do the job for you.</p>', 'It’s vital for any car owner to secure their cars and be protected at all times. In the past, keys were simply keys that are used to open the locks and start the cars. Today, keys have chips inside them such as key fobs and transponder keys.', 'page', 'Programmable Car Keys Replacement', 'It’s vital for any car owner to secure their cars and be protected at all times. In the past, keys were simply keys that are used to open the locks and start the cars. Today, keys have chips inside them such as key fobs and transponder keys.', NULL, NULL, NULL, 'admin', 1, 1, '2017-10-16 03:48:42', '2017-10-17 04:42:06'),
(47, 'Car Key Programming', 'car-key-programming', '<h3>Replacement Car Keys With Chips</h3>\r\n<p>Transponder keys have been around since the mid-1990s. Since then, almost all cars operate with transponder keys and car theft incidents has decreased because of the improved security.</p>\r\n<p>A transponder key contains a chip inside that is used to transmit a signal to the receiver that is located inside of the ignition. With each chip has their unique code, the car can be started if the correct code was sent. If the wrong code was transmitted to the receiver of the car, then the car is unable to be started. This could be a very frustrating experience if you lost your car key.</p>\r\n<p>Replacing a car key with a chip is not easy as replacing a regular key. You can replace your keys by going to a dealership but it can get expensive, and it takes time just to replace your key. Not to mention the towing service you have to pay to take your car to the dealership.</p>\r\n<p>But you still have another choice, and that is hiring a professional locksmith. Car keys with chips inside are not a problem for a locksmith because they have the equipment and tools to provide a new key. Not to worry about the chip because a locksmith also can program chips ensuring you that you&rsquo;ll have a fully functional key that will match to your car. This is surely a more affordable way to replace your car key than going to a dealership.</p>', 'A transponder key contains a chip inside that is used to transmit a signal to the receiver that is located inside of the ignition. With each chip has their unique code, the car can be started if the correct code was sent. ', 'page', 'Car Key Programming, Replacement Car Keys With Chips', 'A transponder key contains a chip inside that is used to transmit a signal to the receiver that is located inside of the ignition. With each chip has their unique code, the car can be started if the correct code was sent. ', NULL, NULL, NULL, 'admin', 1, 1, '2017-10-16 03:49:30', '2017-10-17 04:44:01'),
(48, 'High Security Residential Locks', 'high-security-residential-locks', '<h3>High-Security Residential Locks</h3>\r\n<p>If you take security and safety seriously, you should first start looking at your front door and its locks. Regular locks are like no locks at all. You could be putting your family and possessions&rsquo; at risk. Even an amateur can pick these locks in a matter of seconds. And people with no skills can just use brute force to break these locks. Knowing these locks could compromise your security, the best solution for this is installing high-security locks.</p>\r\n<p>Just like how they are called, high-security locks are much better than regular locks. They are remarkably secure and reliable because they are made of high-quality materials like hardened steel. All of these have high resistance against jimmy objects or any form of physical attack. You can assure that your family and home will be safe against any break-ins.</p>\r\n<p>With high-security locks, you can sleep peacefully at night and have a peace of mind that no intruder will break in your home. They are hard to pick and great for resisting drill attack. Not to mention their long lasting materials to provide you years of protection and security. So don&rsquo;t just go for any old regular locks, replace them with high-security locks to avoid any risks of intruders.</p>', 'Just like how they are called, high-security locks are much better than regular locks. They are remarkably secure and reliable because they are made of high-quality materials like hardened steel. ', 'page', 'High Security Residential Locks', 'Just like how they are called, high-security locks are much better than regular locks. They are remarkably secure and reliable because they are made of high-quality materials like hardened steel. ', NULL, NULL, NULL, 'admin', 1, 1, '2017-10-16 03:49:45', '2017-10-17 04:45:22'),
(49, 'Car Key Cutting', 'car-key-cutting', '<h3>Car Key Cutting And Programming</h3>\r\n<p>For once as a car owner, we need to have our keys cut and programmed. It could be because we lose them, damaged them, or we just need to have a copy. But some cars today require keys that have chips inside them. These are either remote controllers, key fobs, or transponder keys. These special type of keys have transmissions inside them that emit signals to their cars. And each chip has their unique code that corresponds to their matching cars.</p>\r\n<p>When these keys inserted into the ignition, as long as the code is correct, the car will start. Otherwise, if the wrong code was used, the car will not start. So if you need your car keys to be replaced or duplicated, you can go to your dealer. It is a good idea until you will realize that it is expensive and can take a few weeks to receive your key.</p>\r\n<p>Instead, you can go to your local professional locksmith to have your key cut and programmed. Whether or not you have the original key you want to be duplicated; a reputable locksmith can do the job done. He&rsquo;ll provide you the key, have it cut and then program it with his specialized tools and equipment.</p>\r\n<p>Not only this is cheaper, but it''s also more convenient too because some locksmiths offer mobile services. They can go to your location and receive your key on the same day.</p>', 'Whether or not you have the original key you want to be duplicated; a reputable locksmith can do the job done. He’ll provide you the key, have it cut and then program it with his specialized tools and equipment.', 'page', 'Car Key Cutting, Car Key Cutting And Programming', 'Whether or not you have the original key you want to be duplicated; a reputable locksmith can do the job done. He’ll provide you the key, have it cut and then program it with his specialized tools and equipment.', NULL, NULL, NULL, 'admin', 1, 1, '2017-10-16 03:50:31', '2017-10-17 04:46:43');
